# Extractor (Stage 1)

When the user invokes **`Extract Call Records for [CustomerName]`** (or clearly the same intent), follow **`docs/ai/playbooks/extract-call-records.md`** end-to-end.

**`_TEST_CUSTOMER` E2E override (test-only):** when this extraction is part of **`Run E2E Test Customer`** for **`_TEST_CUSTOMER`**, skip approval pauses and execute **`write_call_record`** directly. See **`docs/ai/playbooks/e2e-test-customer.md`**.

## Authority and validation

- **Canonical schema:** `docs/project_spec.md` **§7.1 Per-Call Record**. On-disk validation is enforced by **`prestonotes_mcp/call_records.py`** (`CALL_RECORD_SCHEMA`, `validate_call_record_object`). Every record you assemble **must** pass that schema or MCP **`write_call_record`** will fail.
- **Call types:** Only these **`call_type`** values are allowed: `discovery`, `technical_deep_dive`, `campaign`, `exec_qbr`, `poc_readout`, `renewal`, `internal`. Classification rubric: **`docs/ai/references/call-type-taxonomy.md`**.
- **`call_id`:** Must match the **`write_call_record`** argument and **`record_json.call_id`** exactly. Safe basename only (letters, digits, `._-`); no path segments. Prefer **`YYYY-MM-DD-<type>-<n>`** aligned with the filename stem when one meeting maps to one transcript file.
- **`raw_transcript_ref`:** Basename of the per-call **`.txt`** source (e.g. `2026-04-15-chain-guard.txt`), not a full path.

## Field discipline

- **`participants`:** Only people who appear or are named in the transcript; use `role` / `company` when stated or clearly inferable — otherwise empty string or omit optional keys if your JSON still validates. Do not fabricate executives.
- **`verbatim_quotes`:** At most **3** entries; each **`quote`** must be a **substring** of the transcript (trim whitespace only).
- **`challenges_mentioned`:** Use stable ids **`ch-001`**, **`ch-002`**, … for this meeting. **`status`** should follow §7.4 vocabulary when possible (`identified`, `acknowledged`, `in_progress`, `resolved`, `reopened`, `stalled`).
- **`deltas_from_prior_call`:** If **`read_call_records`** returns prior calls, summarize factual deltas vs the immediately previous chronological record; otherwise `[]`.
- **`extraction_confidence`:** `high` | `medium` | `low` — document reason in run notes if not `high` (e.g. partial transcript, overlapping meetings in one file).

## Sentiment (vocabulary)

Use one of: **`positive`**, **`neutral`**, **`cautious`**, **`negative`**. Pick the best fit from customer tone and outcomes discussed.

## Sources

- **Preferred:** One meeting per file under **`MyNotes/Customers/[Customer]/Transcripts/`** (Granola export pattern `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.txt` per `scripts/granola-sync.py`).
- **`_MASTER_TRANSCRIPT_*.txt`:** Do **not** load entire masters into context. If only masters exist, stop and tell the user to run per-call export / split first, **unless** they explicitly instruct a **bounded** excerpt (max length stated in the playbook step).

## Output

Produce **compact JSON** objects ready for **`write_call_record`**. For normal (non-E2E) runs: after user approval, write **one file per meeting**. For the `_TEST_CUSTOMER` E2E override, execute without waiting for approval.

